forgetting something?

128
00:08:24,570 --> 00:08:25,870
What?

129
00:08:27,204 --> 00:08:29,371
I thought you had something to give me.

130
00:08:30,004 --> 00:08:31,371
I don't.

131
00:08:31,371 --> 00:08:34,371
I've been looking forward
to it all this time.

132
00:08:34,371 --> 00:08:37,104
Don't look forward to anything.

133
00:08:37,104 --> 00:08:40,104
There's no comeback kiss
or any other kiss for that matter.

134
00:08:40,603 --> 00:08:42,237
Comeback kiss?

135
00:08:42,237 --> 00:08:44,371
What are you talking about?
I mean my present.

136
00:08:44,371 --> 00:08:46,171
Aren't you going to give me
my birthday present?

137
00:08:47,371 --> 00:08:49,037
Oh...

138
00:08:49,037 --> 00:08:52,304
Oh, your birthday present. I forgot.

139
00:08:54,904 --> 00:08:56,737
Happy birthday.

140
00:09:03,870 --> 00:09:07,137
A watch with KKJ engraved on it.

141
00:09:08,970 --> 00:09:11,470
Don't you like it?

142
00:09:12,171 --> 00:09:14,104
Put it on for me.

143
00:09:14,104 --> 00:09:17,603
This is the first thing you've
ever given me. Make it count.

144
00:09:17,603 --> 00:09:19,104
Let's not make ado about nothing.

145
00:09:19,104 --> 00:09:21,371
Why don't you just cuff me?

146
00:09:21,371 --> 00:09:24,171
You'll then have all the time
in the world with me.

147
00:09:24,904 --> 00:09:27,104
If that's what this will mean, I can't do it.

148
00:09:27,104 --> 00:09:29,804
Just think of it as nothing but
a birthday gift, and you put it on.

149
00:09:31,004 --> 00:09:34,004
If you don't put it on for me,
I'm not coming onboard.

150
00:09:35,804 --> 00:09:37,837
This won't do.

151
00:09:40,404 --> 00:09:42,338
Look at the watch.

152
00:09:42,870 --> 00:09:46,804
Relax and focus on the watch.

153
00:09:48,670 --> 00:09:51,570
Let me out here.

154
00:09:52,737 --> 00:09:55,837
It's 10:10.

155
00:09:55,837 --> 00:10:00,503
Remember where the hands are.

156
00:10:00,503 --> 00:10:05,237
From now on, whenever the watch says 10:10,

157
00:10:05,237 --> 00:10:07,670
you will think of KKJ.

158
00:10:07,670 --> 00:10:12,837
Gil Da Ran will think of KKJ.

159
00:10:12,837 --> 00:10:15,004
1, 2,

160
00:10:15,004 --> 00:10:16,371
red sun.

161
00:10:16,371 --> 00:10:18,171
What's going on?

162
00:10:18,770 --> 00:10:21,071
You've just been hypnotized.

163
00:10:21,071 --> 00:10:25,071
Every time the watch reads
10:10, twice a day,

164
00:10:25,071 --> 00:10:27,603
you will think of me no matter what.

165
00:10:27,603 --> 00:10:29,237
It'll be like that for the rest of your life.

166
00:10:29,237 --> 00:10:30,570
No way.

167
00:10:30,570 --> 00:10:32,104
We'll see.

168
00:10:32,104 --> 00:10:35,104
People who are timid and indecisive
become hypnotized more easily.

169
00:10:35,104 --> 00:10:36,804
You're making me worried.

170
00:10:36,804 --> 00:10:38,304
Snap me out of it. Red sun.

171
00:10:38,304 --> 00:10:42,171
The hypnosis must've worked
seeing that you're nervous.

172
00:10:42,171 --> 00:10:44,171
And that means you'll stay with me.

173
00:10:44,970 --> 00:10:46,570
Get me out of it.

174
00:10:46,570 --> 00:10:48,870
Red sun. Snap me back.

175
00:10:48,870 --> 00:10:50,137
Hey.

176
00:10:50,137 --> 00:10:52,004
Are you trying to catch a fly?

177
00:10:55,837 --> 00:10:57,204
Snap me out of it.

178
00:10:57,204 --> 00:10:58,470
No one can break the hypnosis but me.

179
00:10:58,470 --> 00:11:00,204
I know. Red sun. Sun. Sun.

180
00:11:00,204 --> 00:11:01,371
Alright. Fine.

181
00:11:01,371 --> 00:11:03,071
Blue sun.

182
00:11:03,071 --> 00:11:04,237
Black sun.

183
00:11:04,237 --> 00:11:07,603
- White sun.
- No. Snap me out.

184
00:11:07,603 --> 00:11:09,470
It's bothering me.

185
00:11:09,470 --> 00:11:11,104
No.

186
00:11:11,104 --> 00:11:12,704
Wait inside.

187
00:11:13,438 --> 00:11:17,470
I threw out your toothbrush, because
you had said you were leaving.

188
00:11:17,470 --> 00:11:18,904
I'll go and get you a new one.

189
00:11:18,904 --> 00:11:20,937
When did you throw out my toothbrush?

190
00:11:20,937 --> 00:11:23,004
I also threw out your slippers.

191
00:11:24,670 --> 00:11:26,837
Get a carton of milk too.

192
00:11:27,304 --> 00:11:29,171
Okay.

193
00:11:29,637 --> 00:11:31,171
10:10.

194
00:11:31,904 --> 00:11:33,670
Gotcha.

195
00:11:35,371 --> 00:11:37,071
I gotcha. I gotcha.

196
00:11:43,904 --> 00:11:46,004
Mary.

197
00:11:49,304 --> 00:11:52,670
Did you get that for Gyeong Jun
for his birthday?

198
00:11:52,670 --> 00:11:55,637
Huh? Yeah.

199
00:11:55,637 --> 00:11:57,338
You should go on inside.

200
00:11:57,338 --> 00:12:00,970
I have to tell Gyeong Jun
something very important.

201
00:12:00,970 --> 00:12:03,237
Then come in with me
and wait for him inside.

202
00:12:03,237 --> 00:12:06,670
It's something important about
Gyeong Jun that only I know.

203
00:12:06,670 --> 00:12:08,804
You stay out of it.

204
00:12:16,304 --> 00:12:18,004
Gyeong Jun.

205
00:12:19,438 --> 00:12:21,937
I kept calling you yesterday.
Why didn't you pick up?

206
00:12:21,937 --> 00:12:24,970
You kept insisting on throwing a party,
and I didn't want you to do that.

207
00:12:24,970 --> 00:12:27,037
I just wasn't in the mood.

208
00:12:27,770 --> 00:12:31,937
Are you in a better mood now
because of Ms. Gil?

209
00:12:31,937 --> 00:12:33,338
Yup.

210
00:12:34,371 --> 00:12:38,137
Then if I tell you something sad,
I'll put you in a funk again.

211
00:12:38,937 --> 00:12:40,904
It's okay. You can tell me.

212
00:12:40,904 --> 00:12:43,904
I'm so happy right now that
a bit of bad news won't hurt.

213
00:12:44,770 --> 00:12:46,371
Are you that happy?

214
00:12:46,371 --> 00:12:47,937
Yup.

215
00:12:53,737 --> 00:12:56,037
So what is it?

216
00:12:56,037 --> 00:12:57,670
No.

217
00:12:57,670 --> 00:13:00,338
I don't want to tell you anything bad.

218
00:13:00,338 --> 00:13:02,603
I'll have Ms. Gil tell you.

219
00:13:02,603 --> 00:13:06,137
Sounds good. It would be better
coming from Gil Teacher anyway.

220
00:13:07,404 --> 00:13:09,438
This looks good.

221
00:13:14,271 --> 00:13:18,171
Once Ms. Gil finds out who your father is,

222
00:13:18,937 --> 00:13:21,537
neither of you will be laughing anymore.

223
00:13:27,670 --> 00:13:30,670
[Roundtrip Ticket to the Moon A-1]

224
00:13:32,970 --> 00:13:34,870
A trip to the moon.

225
00:13:35,603 --> 00:13:38,071
A submarine adventure.

226
00:13:42,304 --> 00:13:44,870
Will we ever get to do such things?

227
00:13:46,937 --> 00:13:50,503
Gyeong Jun, it's all thanks to you
that I'm visiting the moon.

228
00:13:50,503 --> 00:13:53,970
We can't even see the Great Wall from here.

229
00:13:53,970 --> 00:13:57,004
It makes me realize how trivial the worries

230
00:13:57,004 --> 00:13:58,870
I had on Earth were.

231
00:13:58,870 --> 00:14:01,237
I'm glad I kicked them all aside.

232
00:14:09,104 --> 00:14:12,670
Gyeong Jun, thanks for bringing me
on the submarine adventure.

233
00:14:12,670 --> 00:14:15,804
Thanks also for telling me we had a future.

234
00:14:27,171 --> 00:14:29,171
Gyeong Jun.

235
00:14:43,037 --> 00:14:44,770
How's it going?

236
00:14:46,037 --> 00:14:47,670
Good.

237
00:14:51,937 --> 00:14:54,837
Where did you get these?

238
00:14:56,570 --> 00:14:58,603
Birthday present from Jang Mary.

239
00:14:59,704 --> 00:15:02,770
She had all the kids at school
enter a smart phone sweepstakes,

240
00:15:02,770 --> 00:15:04,870
and one of the kids won all these drinks.

241
00:15:08,603 --> 00:15:13,603
When Mary sets her mind to something,
she's like an express train.

242
00:15:13,603 --> 00:15:15,704
