even run on well-laid tracks.

251
00:15:43,970 --> 00:15:45,737
You got this again?

252
00:15:45,737 --> 00:15:47,438
I'm sick and tired of this one.

253
00:15:47,438 --> 00:15:49,470
Wasn't there anything new?

254
00:15:49,470 --> 00:15:50,804
But you said you liked that bread.

255
00:15:51,670 --> 00:15:52,970
Let's get something else.

256
00:15:52,970 --> 00:15:58,071
Kids tend to tire of things easily.

257
00:15:59,304 --> 00:16:01,404
Are you commiserating with the bread?

258
00:16:01,404 --> 00:16:02,804
No.

259
00:16:02,804 --> 00:16:06,271
I'll eat the bread for energy
and charge ahead on my tracks.

260
00:16:06,271 --> 00:16:08,737
My tracks will be laid toward
the high school in Pocheon,

261
00:16:08,737 --> 00:16:12,104
and I'm going to charge ahead
toward my dim and quaint future.

